'''''The Last Ottoman''''' ({{lang-tr|Son Osmanl<U+0131> Yand<U+0131>m Ali}}) is a 2007 Turkish [[action film]] directed by [[Mustafa <U+015E>evki Do<U+011F>an]]. The film, based on the based on the comic book by [[Suat Yalaz]], tells the story of Tahtac<U+0131>zade "Yand<U+0131>m" Ali who is inspired by the landing of [[Mustafa Kemal Atat<U+00FC>rk|Mustafa Kemal]] at [[Samsun]] and decides to join the resistance movement fighting against the occupation of [[Istanbul]] in the aftermath of the [[First World War]]. The film went on general release across Turkey on {{start date|2007|01|19}} and is the fourth highest grossing [[Turkish films of 2007|Turkish film of 2007]].<ref name="HDN01">{{cite web |title=New films of the week |first= |last= |coauthors= |url=http://www.hurriyetdailynews.com/h.php?news=new-films-of-the-week-2007-01-20 |work=[[H<U+00FC>rriyet Daily News]] |date=2007-01-20 |accessdate=2010-08-12 }}</ref>

==Plot==
The film is set in the years after [[World War I]] when the Ottoman capital of [[Istanbul]] was under the siege by the enemy. A navy sergeant named Ali ([[Kenan <U+0130>mirzal<U+0131>o<U+011F>lu]]), who has just completed his military service, is yearning for his fianc<U+00E9>e Defne ([[Cansu Dere]]) who married another man while Ali was away. Ali plans to abduct Defne and flee to [[Vienna]]. However, Ali's plans change when he comes across [[Mustafa Kemal Atat<U+00FC>rk|Mustafa Kemal]], who has just set on a journey to save the Turkish land from the enemy. Ali recognizes that his real love is his country, and joins in the endeavors to save his country.

